multiple common share classes, market capitalization includes both classes. Shares Outstanding Number of shares that are currently held by investors, including restricted shares owned by the company's officers and insiders as well as those held by the public. Public Float The number of shares in the hands of public investors and available to trade. To calculate, start with total shares outstanding and subtract the number of restricted shares. Restricted stock typically is that issued to company insiders with limits on when it may be traded. Dividend Yield A company's dividend expressed as a percentage of its current stock price.      Key Stock Data    P/E Ratio (TTM) N/A     EPS (TTM)  $-3.65      Market Cap $4.32 B     Shares Outstanding 985.75 M     Public Float 972.80 M     Yield WFT has not issued dividends in more than 1 year.     Latest Dividend N/A     Ex-Dividend Date N/A       ?    Shares Sold Short The total number of shares of a security that have been sold short and not yet repurchased. Change from Last Percentage change in short interest from the previous report to the most recent report. Exchanges report short interest twice a month. Percent of Float Total short positions relative to the number of shares available to trade.      Short Interest (06/30/17)    Shares Sold Short 153.89 M     Change from Last  3.75%      Percent of Float 15.82%       ?    Money Flow Uptick/Downtick Ratio Money flow measures the relative buying and selling pressure on a stock, based on the value of trades made on an "uptick" in price and the value of trades made on a "downtick" in price. The up/down ratio is calculated by dividing the value of uptick trades by the value of downtick trades. Net money flow is the value of uptick trades minus the value of downtick trades. Our calculations are based on comprehensive, delayed quotes.      Stock Money Flow    Uptick/Downtick Trade Ratio  0 2    1.31      Net Money Flow ($)  2.43 M    Money flow gives a snapshot of relative buying and selling pressure in a stock. A ratio above one suggests greater buying pressure, below one suggests greater selling.               Advertisement         Competitors WFT      Company Change P/E (TTM)    TESO Tesco Corp.   -4.26% -0.20   -     SLB Schlumberger Ltd.   -0.73% -0.49   511.77     DOV Dover Corp.   -0.36% -0.30   20.78     HAL Halliburton Co.   -2.20% -1.00   -     FTK Flotek Industries Inc.   -3.61% -0.32   -     FET Forum Energy Technologies Inc.   -4.53% -0.70   -     FI Frank's International N.V.   -6.31% -0.57   -     BHGE Baker Hughes, a GE co. Cl A   -2.43% -0.85   -        More information on WFT   Competitor Data Provided By: capital cube           Profile WFT      Weatherford International Plc provides equipment and services to the oil and natural gas exploration and production industry. It operates its business through the following business groups: Formation Evaluation & Well Construction, Completion & Production and Land Drilling...      Weststrasse 1 Baar Zug 6340 Switzerland   Website Map       Employees  30,000    Sector  Oil & Gas Products/Services      Sales or Revenue  5.75 B    Industry  Companies on the Energy Service      1Y Sales Change  -39.05%    Fiscal Year Ends December 31 Download Reports          Mark A. McCollum President, Chief Executive Officer & Director       Christoph Bausch Chief Financial Officer & Executive Vice President       Mario Ruscev CTO, Executive VP & President-Product Lines       Frederico Justus President-Regional Operations        More             Research & Ratings Weatherford International Ltd.WFT Per-Share Earnings, Actuals and Estimates      Quarterly   Annual    WFT will report FY 2017 earnings on 02/27/2018   WFT will report Q2 earnings on 07/27/2017         Actual     Analyst Range     Consensus      0.20  0.00  -0.20  -0.40              Actual -0.28     -0.30           Actual -0.39     -0.25           Actual -0.32     -0.34           Actual -0.32     -0.31        -0.28        -0.22       Q22016 